  "figshare_url": "https://bridges.monash.edu/articles/thesis/Real-World_Outcomes_for_Women_with_Ovarian_Cancer_Measuring_Quality_of_Care_in_Australia_Using_a_Clinical_Quality_Registry/32526309",
  "download_disabled": false,
  "description": "Ovarian cancer is Australia\u2019s deadliest gynaecological cancer, and survival depends heavily on the quality of treatment received. This PhD utilised the National Gynae-Oncology Registry (NGOR) to provide the first comprehensive assessment of patterns of care standards nationwide. The research confirmed that adhering to best-practice guidelines -  specifically high-quality surgery, standard chemotherapy, and genetic testing significantly improves survival. However, the studies identified critical disparities: older women often receive less intensive treatment, and the uptake of new life-prolonging targeted therapies is inconsistent. This work provides evidence needed to improve standards and ensure equitable, life-saving care for all Australian women.",
